issues.body:
### Problem

The current implementation for labeling user activities using Gemini AI sometimes results in ambiguous, inconsistent, or incomplete category assignments. Activity labels are generated in `server/services/geminiService.js` (see the `categorizeActivity` and `batchCategorize` methods), and used in several places in the backend (see `server/controllers/activity.controller.js`). However, there are cases where:
- The AI categorization fails or returns low confidence, and fallback logic applies generic or 'Unknown' categories.
- Similar activities (by domain or title) may receive inconsistent categories or tags due to insufficient normalization or context.
- Some activities remain uncategorized (`categoryName: { $exists: false }`) and require recategorization (see `recategorizeActivities` and batch logic).

### Suggested Improvements

- Enhance Gemini prompt engineering in `categorizeActivity` to force more precise, context-aware responses, especially for edge cases such as multi-purpose domains (e.g., YouTube, Reddit).
- Improve normalization and deduplication logic for titles/domains before sending to Gemini, to reduce inconsistent labeling.
- Track and report the rate of fallback categorizations and 'Unknown' assignments; consider alerting or logging for review.
- Add or update tests to simulate ambiguous activities and verify that Gemini consistently produces correct, specific labels.
- Ensure batch recategorization (`batchCategorize`) can handle and correct existing unlabeled or miscategorized activities.
- Document expected label structure and Gemini's response contract in code comments.

### Relevant code files:
- [server/services/geminiService.js](https://github.com/nst-sdc/Screentime-recoder/blob/3f3ea550b08b5517028f263e67302099e0912b4c/server/services/geminiService.js) — core Gemini logic, fallback, and batch.
- [server/controllers/activity.controller.js](https://github.com/nst-sdc/Screentime-recoder/blob/3f3ea550b08b5517028f263e67302099e0912b4c/server/controllers/activity.controller.js) — handles activity creation, logging, and recategorization with Gemini.
- [server/models/activity.model.js](https://github.com/nst-sdc/Screentime-recoder/blob/3f3ea550b08b5517028f263e67302099e0912b4c/server/models/activity.model.js) — schema for categories and AI analysis fields.

### Acceptance Criteria
- Activities are consistently labeled with clear, context-aware categories.
- Fallbacks and 'Unknown' assignments are minimized and logged.
- New or updated tests exist for edge cases and batch recategorization.
- Documentation is updated for developers.

### Priority
This is important for accurate analytics and productivity insights.

